00:22:17.450 --> 00:22:22.250
did you extract scriptural principles from accounts

00:22:22.250 --> 00:22:25.369
and then talk about a practical application

00:22:25.369 --> 00:22:27.369
of those principles?

00:22:27.369 --> 00:22:32.250
Those principles are now like a spool of spiritual thread

00:22:32.250 --> 00:22:35.410
that you can use to strengthen your brothers and sisters.

00:22:37.130 --> 00:22:40.089
At times the needs of others may seem very small

00:22:40.089 --> 00:22:44.930
or insignificant or even something they should just get over.

00:22:46.210 --> 00:22:49.170
Yet when you unselfishly stop what you're doing

00:22:49.170 --> 00:22:51.210
and fill those needs,

00:22:51.210 --> 00:22:56.130
it will be like putting tiny stitches in the seam of a garment.

00:22:56.130 --> 00:22:59.210
Those you help will be stronger and in turn,

00:22:59.210 --> 00:23:02.529
they will use that strength to help others

00:23:02.529 --> 00:23:04.089
in Jehovah's organization.

00:23:05.049 --> 00:23:07.410
Often of course the stitches we put in

00:23:07.410 --> 00:23:10.849
to strengthen others are made with our tongue.

00:23:10.849 --> 00:23:13.450
And like a sewing needle, our tongue is very sharp.

00:23:14.569 --> 00:23:16.690
Proverbs 12, 18 says,

00:23:16.690 --> 00:23:19.089
thoughtless speech is like the stabs of a sword

00:23:19.089 --> 00:23:21.890
but the tongue of the wise ones is a healing.

00:23:21.890 --> 00:23:26.130
And I think you would all agree that while we have healed

00:23:26.130 --> 00:23:27.849
people with our tongue at times,

00:23:27.849 --> 00:23:30.210
we've also done a little bit of stabbing

00:23:30.210 --> 00:23:32.730
along the way as well and a thoughtless way.

00:23:33.650 --> 00:23:35.569
Now you're going to see that as you gain

00:23:35.569 --> 00:23:37.130
more responsibility,

00:23:38.690 --> 00:23:42.529
the words you say will have even greater impact

00:23:42.529 --> 00:23:43.890
than they have in the past.

00:23:44.769 --> 00:23:45.849
So the question is,

00:23:45.849 --> 00:23:50.369
our theme, will your tiny stitches strengthen others?

00:23:51.289 --> 00:23:53.450
We're going to discuss four scriptures

00:23:53.450 --> 00:23:56.809
that highlight ways you can put in stitches

00:23:56.809 --> 00:23:58.289
that will strengthen others.

00:23:59.569 --> 00:24:02.130
The first example is found in Jesus' illustration

00:24:02.130 --> 00:24:02.970
of the talents.

00:24:02.970 --> 00:24:04.609
That's found in Matthew 25,

00:24:04.609 --> 00:24:06.490
but you'll remember it,

00:24:06.490 --> 00:24:10.809
as the master returns and reviews the work of his slaves,

00:24:10.809 --> 00:24:13.849
he uses the exact same wording for two of his slaves.

00:24:13.849 --> 00:24:15.049
He says,

00:24:15.049 --> 00:24:18.329
well done, good and faithful slave.

00:24:18.329 --> 00:24:20.690
Enter into the joy of your master.

00:24:21.529 --> 00:24:24.730
Well, as we heard highlighted already by our chairman,

00:24:24.730 --> 00:24:27.170
commendation is powerful,

00:24:28.250 --> 00:24:30.970
but it's not automatically strengthening.

00:24:30.970 --> 00:24:32.529
Have you ever had the circumstances

00:24:32.529 --> 00:24:33.650
where you are busy working

00:24:33.690 --> 00:24:35.809
and someone walks by and says,

00:24:35.809 --> 00:24:37.369
keep up your good work.

00:24:37.369 --> 00:24:39.170
And you're thinking to yourself,

00:24:39.170 --> 00:24:41.289
do they even know what work I do?

00:24:42.970 --> 00:24:45.609
For commendation to be strengthening,

00:24:45.609 --> 00:24:48.730
it must be sincere, it must be specific.

00:24:49.730 --> 00:24:52.529
The publication, keep yourself in God's love,

00:24:52.529 --> 00:24:53.930
expressed it this way.

00:24:54.970 --> 00:24:57.930
A sincere word of commendation lets you know

00:24:57.930 --> 00:25:00.250
that someone notices you,

00:25:00.250 --> 00:25:03.210
that someone cares about you,

00:25:03.210 --> 00:25:06.809
and that what you did was well worth the effort involved.

00:25:06.809 --> 00:25:09.170
Such reassurance builds your confidence

00:25:09.170 --> 00:25:13.289
and motivates you to work even more diligently in the future.

00:25:14.490 --> 00:25:16.289
What's that telling us?

00:25:16.289 --> 00:25:19.809
That every time you sincerely commend someone

00:25:19.809 --> 00:25:21.250
for what they're doing,

00:25:21.250 --> 00:25:25.130
you're putting in tiny stitches that strengthens them.

00:25:25.130 --> 00:25:26.490
Example number two.

00:25:27.410 --> 00:25:29.089
Proverbs 12-25 says,

00:25:29.089 --> 00:25:32.930
anxiety in a man's heart weighs it down,

00:25:32.970 --> 00:25:34.690
but a good word cheers it up.

00:25:35.769 --> 00:25:39.849
Well, those who are anxious or discouraged

00:25:39.849 --> 00:25:42.049
need encouragement.

00:25:42.049 --> 00:25:45.769
They need to know that you see what they're dealing with,

00:25:45.769 --> 00:25:49.529
that you care about them and that you want to help.

00:25:49.529 --> 00:25:51.369
As the watch star once put it,

00:25:51.369 --> 00:25:53.049
at this point in the race for life,

00:25:53.049 --> 00:25:55.569
our brothers need not critics,

00:25:55.569 --> 00:25:59.609
but friends to cheer them on to victory, well said.

00:25:59.609 --> 00:26:02.170
Each and every time you use the principles

00:26:02.170 --> 00:26:04.529
you have learned from God's word,

00:26:04.529 --> 00:26:08.609
to encourage someone to cheer up their heart that's weighed down,

00:26:09.650 --> 00:26:12.730
you're putting in tiny stitches that make them stronger.

00:26:13.849 --> 00:26:14.930
Example three.

00:26:16.289 --> 00:26:18.569
Galatians 6-1 says in part,

00:26:18.569 --> 00:26:21.809
if a man takes a false step before he's aware of it,

00:26:21.809 --> 00:26:24.769
try to readjust him in a spirit of mildness.

00:26:25.809 --> 00:26:30.130
You know, counsel can be embarrassing.

00:26:30.170 --> 00:26:31.849
It can be embarrassing to receive,

00:26:31.849 --> 00:26:36.250
but frankly, it can also be embarrassing to give to others.

00:26:36.250 --> 00:26:40.130
And at times, it's unnecessarily embarrassing

00:26:40.130 --> 00:26:43.569
because the one who gives the counsel waited far too long

00:26:43.569 --> 00:26:44.569
to speak up.

00:26:45.890 --> 00:26:50.450
Why not make it your aim to give lots and lots

00:26:50.450 --> 00:26:53.210
of tiny reminders?

00:26:53.210 --> 00:26:55.049
In English, there's a saying,

00:26:55.049 --> 00:26:57.930
a stitch in time saves time.

00:26:57.930 --> 00:26:59.650
What does that mean?

00:26:59.690 --> 00:27:03.490
It means that when a small mistake is corrected,

00:27:03.490 --> 00:27:05.170
that it never gets larger,

00:27:05.170 --> 00:27:08.250
and it never requires all the time and effort

00:27:08.250 --> 00:27:10.569
to correct it that it would have taken

00:27:10.569 --> 00:27:12.210
if it had gotten larger.

00:27:13.009 --> 00:27:16.289
When you give others reminders in a spirit of mildness,

00:27:16.289 --> 00:27:20.210
and they sense that you genuinely care about them,

00:27:20.210 --> 00:27:23.529
you put in stitches that will strengthen them greatly.

00:27:24.569 --> 00:27:25.970
Example number four.

00:27:26.970 --> 00:27:30.250
After the faithful man Job was approved for his wrong viewpoint,

00:27:30.250 --> 00:27:32.490
he says, I make a retraction,

00:27:32.490 --> 00:27:36.690
and I do repent in dust and ashes.

00:27:36.690 --> 00:27:38.730
Well, his brother let emphasized,

00:27:38.730 --> 00:27:42.289
an apology is a powerful thing.

00:27:43.410 --> 00:27:47.049
But how is it also strengthening to others?

00:27:47.049 --> 00:27:48.049
Let's illustrate.

00:27:49.130 --> 00:27:51.529
