00:28:02.250 --> 00:28:05.369
and he sincerely apologized to the brothers.

00:28:05.369 --> 00:28:06.930
Well, what was the result of that?

00:28:06.930 --> 00:28:09.250
Did they all lose their respect for the brother?

00:28:09.250 --> 00:28:12.049
Did they suggest that maybe he wasn't qualified

00:28:12.049 --> 00:28:13.769
for his assignment anymore?

00:28:13.769 --> 00:28:15.210
Not at all.

00:28:15.210 --> 00:28:17.369
One brother who was there said,

00:28:17.369 --> 00:28:19.450
when I saw him admit his mistake

00:28:19.450 --> 00:28:23.130
in front of all those elders, it impressed me greatly.

00:28:23.130 --> 00:28:26.930
I respected him a lot more after that apology.

00:28:26.930 --> 00:28:29.490
His example taught me how important it is

00:28:29.490 --> 00:28:31.849
to recognize my own shortcomings.

00:28:32.930 --> 00:28:35.369
So if it will be your pattern

00:28:35.369 --> 00:28:38.490
to humbly admit your mistakes and apologize,

00:28:38.490 --> 00:28:40.569
others will respect you more,

00:28:40.569 --> 00:28:43.009
but it will also build their respect

00:28:43.009 --> 00:28:45.250
and love for Jehovah's organization.

00:28:46.410 --> 00:28:48.250
These may not seem like big things

00:28:48.250 --> 00:28:51.089
in some ways they're not, to command,

00:28:51.089 --> 00:28:56.089
to encourage, to give loving reminders or to apologize.

00:28:56.410 --> 00:28:59.250
However, please never underestimate

00:28:59.250 --> 00:29:03.890
the strengthening effect of every little tiny stitch

00:29:03.890 --> 00:29:06.450
that you put in to strengthen your brothers.

00:29:06.450 --> 00:29:08.650
And brothers, especially for you,

00:29:09.650 --> 00:29:13.890
never forget the value of the freeness of speech

00:29:13.890 --> 00:29:15.849
that so doing will bring to you

00:29:15.849 --> 00:29:18.569
when you have to handle weighty matters

00:29:18.569 --> 00:29:22.970
or give counsel to individuals or to large audiences.

00:29:22.970 --> 00:29:26.609
No fair warning, as you make thousands

00:29:26.609 --> 00:29:29.130
of tiny stitches to strengthen others,

00:29:29.130 --> 00:29:32.650
unselfishly applying what Philippians chapter two said,

00:29:33.730 --> 00:29:35.809
your work's not always going to be seen.

00:29:35.809 --> 00:29:37.130
It may be invisible.

00:29:37.130 --> 00:29:40.849
In fact, those you strengthen may not even remember

00:29:40.849 --> 00:29:44.490
that you did so, and that's okay,

00:29:44.490 --> 00:29:46.849
because Jehovah knows.

00:29:46.849 --> 00:29:51.490
Jehovah sees everything you say and everything you do

00:29:51.490 --> 00:29:54.329
to strengthen your brothers and sisters around you.

00:29:54.329 --> 00:29:56.849
And when he looks at his organization,

00:29:56.849 --> 00:29:59.289
he will know that it is stronger,

00:29:59.289 --> 00:30:03.609
that it is more united, that it is increasingly beautiful

00:30:03.609 --> 00:30:07.970
in part at least to the thousands of tiny stitches

00:30:07.970 --> 00:30:23.180
that you have made.

00:30:23.180 --> 00:30:25.819
Well, it's obvious the students really appreciated

00:30:25.819 --> 00:30:28.660
that practical advice.

