but Jacob was determined to stick with Jehovah.

00:53:13.789 --> 00:53:18.070
Even when the journey took him through hard times.

00:53:18.070 --> 00:53:22.989
For example, there was a time in Jacob's life

00:53:22.989 --> 00:53:26.230
that he stumbled into a patch of injustice.

00:53:26.230 --> 00:53:29.989
He wanted to get married on the wedding night.

00:53:29.989 --> 00:53:33.909
His uncle Laban substituted his older planar daughter,

00:53:33.909 --> 00:53:37.190
Leah, for his beloved Rachel.

00:53:38.150 --> 00:53:43.110
Chapter 29 verse 25 describes this scene.

00:53:43.110 --> 00:53:48.090
29, 25.

00:53:48.090 --> 00:53:52.409
In the morning, Jacob saw that it was Leah.

00:53:52.409 --> 00:53:58.650
Now, that is an unexpected turn in his root with Jehovah God.

00:54:00.570 --> 00:54:02.010
But what would Jacob do?

00:54:02.010 --> 00:54:04.889
Here he says to Laban, what have you done to me?

00:54:04.889 --> 00:54:07.449
It was not for Rachel that I served you.

00:54:07.610 --> 00:54:10.010
Why have you tricked me?

00:54:10.010 --> 00:54:11.650
What would Jacob do now?

00:54:11.650 --> 00:54:14.369
Would he rise up in arms against such betrayal?

00:54:14.369 --> 00:54:15.650
It gets worse.

00:54:16.610 --> 00:54:21.050
Verse 26, the very next verse, now Laban makes excuses.

00:54:21.050 --> 00:54:24.369
He makes excuses by saying, it's not our custom

00:54:24.369 --> 00:54:26.409
to give the younger before the older.

00:54:26.409 --> 00:54:28.130
It's not your custom.

00:54:28.130 --> 00:54:32.610
Outrage, Jacob could have said, look, we had a contract.

00:54:32.610 --> 00:54:34.769
I worked seven years for you.

00:54:34.769 --> 00:54:37.210
I've waited 84 years to get married

00:54:37.289 --> 00:54:39.010
and this is what you do to me.

00:54:39.010 --> 00:54:42.849
And now you say, it's not our custom.

00:54:42.849 --> 00:54:45.730
Couldn't you have at least told me ahead of time

00:54:45.730 --> 00:54:49.519
that it's not our custom?

00:54:49.519 --> 00:54:51.800
But how did Jacob respond?

00:54:52.639 --> 00:54:56.280
He agreed to work another seven years.

00:54:56.280 --> 00:54:58.199
Why didn't he walk away?

00:54:58.199 --> 00:55:02.000
Why didn't he walk away from such deceit and mistreatment?

00:55:02.000 --> 00:55:05.760
There's the question, why?

00:55:05.760 --> 00:55:10.760
Because Jacob knew that Jehovah cannot be deceived.

00:55:13.800 --> 00:55:17.760
He understood that Jehovah saw what was happening

00:55:19.000 --> 00:55:24.000
and this knowledge helped Jacob to prefer peace to strife.

00:55:24.280 --> 00:55:27.639
Instead of being stubborn and demanding his rights,

00:55:27.639 --> 00:55:29.840
he left the matter in Jehovah's hands

00:55:29.840 --> 00:55:32.559
confident that he saw what happened

00:55:32.559 --> 00:55:35.559
and that he would handle it in due time.

00:55:36.599 --> 00:55:41.599
And remember, Jacob was not harmed by doing so.

00:55:42.440 --> 00:55:44.800
In fact, in just seven years,

00:55:44.800 --> 00:55:47.880
Jacob was blessed with several children.

00:55:47.880 --> 00:55:50.079
But if he had stood his ground

00:55:50.079 --> 00:55:55.840
and insisted on having only Rachel, I want Rachel.

00:55:55.840 --> 00:55:59.159
He may have only had two sons instead of 12.

00:56:00.159 --> 00:56:05.159
So again, where did this journey with Jehovah take him?

00:56:06.119 --> 00:56:10.280
Jehovah used this wrong to build a great nation out of Jacob.

00:56:11.239 --> 00:56:14.599
The Messiah came through Judah, Judah,

00:56:14.599 --> 00:56:19.599
who was Lee's son, not Rachel's.

00:56:20.519 --> 00:56:24.719
The Messiah was brought forth despite a great injustice.

00:56:24.719 --> 00:56:28.079
You see, Jacob traveled with Jehovah

00:56:28.079 --> 00:56:30.639
and Jehovah brought him to a spiritual place

00:56:30.639 --> 00:56:33.719
he could not get to on his own.

00:56:35.199 --> 00:56:38.920
Now we find Jacob with a 14-year work contract with Laban.

00:56:38.920 --> 00:56:42.239
The next seven years could have embittered Jacob.

00:56:42.239 --> 00:56:46.239
Jacob's own family suffered from jealousy and resentment.

00:56:47.000 --> 00:56:50.679
Laban continued to exploit him by unfairly changing

00:56:50.679 --> 00:56:53.800
his wages 10 times.

00:56:53.800 --> 00:56:56.159
But rather than being fed up,

00:56:56.159 --> 00:57:00.000
he maintained the right spirit and attitude.

00:57:00.000 --> 00:57:01.960
It is amazing this Jacob.

00:57:02.719 --> 00:57:05.480
He didn't adopt a cynical bitter attitude.

00:57:05.480 --> 00:57:09.079
In fact, chapter 31 and verse 6,

00:57:09.079 --> 00:57:14.079
it says that I served Laban with all my power.

00:57:14.840 --> 00:57:18.000
And with all those injustices with all my power,

00:57:19.400 --> 00:57:22.639
because he did not face this test alone.

00:57:22.639 --> 00:57:24.519
He had Jehovah at his side.

00:57:24.519 --> 00:57:25.480
This is the point.

00:57:25.480 --> 00:57:27.480
He was journeying with Jehovah.

00:57:27.480 --> 00:57:29.760
Look at verse 5.

00:57:29.760 --> 00:57:31.599
He sensed it. He knew it.

00:57:31.639 --> 00:57:32.880
He got it.

00:57:32.880 --> 00:57:36.119
The God of my father has been with me.

00:57:36.119 --> 00:57:38.079
Oh, this journey with Jehovah.

00:57:38.079 --> 00:57:41.320
Was it easy? No. Was it possible?

00:57:41.320 --> 00:57:43.840
Yes, he stuck with Jehovah.

00:57:43.840 --> 00:57:46.480
Look to Jehovah for strength.

00:57:47.880 --> 00:57:51.039
Jehovah God wants you and me

00:57:52.199 --> 00:57:54.760
to learn from this true life story.

00:57:55.920 --> 00:57:57.719
Think about it.

00:57:57.719 --> 00:58:02.719
Jehovah could have arranged for Jacob to be born first.

00:58:06.210 --> 00:58:09.210
But consider what Jehovah is teaching us

00:58:09.210 --> 00:58:13.809
by arranging for the older to serve the younger.

00:58:15.130 --> 00:58:18.530
He is teaching us that we don't receive blessings

00:58:18.530 --> 00:58:22.369
through effortless inheritance.

00:58:22.369 --> 00:58:25.969
And this is the lesson we want you to learn.

00:58:25.969 --> 00:58:29.090
That journeying with Jehovah does not mean

00:58:29.090 --> 00:58:32.909
you will have an easy journey.

00:58:32.909 --> 00:58:35.309
But if you stick with Jehovah,

00:58:36.269 --> 00:58:39.269
he will take you to places spiritually,

00:58:39.269 --> 00:58:42.070
you cannot get to on your own.

00:58:43.590 --> 00:58:46.949
So hold on to the promise that Jehovah will reward you

00:58:46.949 --> 00:58:48.989
for doing what is right.

00:58:48.989 --> 00:58:52.230
Even if it means making a temporary sacrifice

00:58:52.230 --> 00:58:57.230
or suffering injustice, leave the matter in Jehovah's hands

00:58:57.349 --> 00:59:02.110
and then pay attention to how he works things out.

00:59:03.309 --> 00:59:07.030
Let Jehovah help you rise above fleshly tendencies

00:59:07.030 --> 00:59:10.110
to look out for self.

00:59:11.230 --> 00:59:14.869
Imitate Jacob, like Jacob, prefer peace to strife.

00:59:15.750 --> 00:59:19.789
For example, at Bethel, your Bethel,

00:59:19.789 --> 00:59:24.789
when you see a department that gets along, there is a cost.

00:59:24.789 --> 00:59:26.429
It's not for free.

00:59:26.429 --> 00:59:29.230
Someone is paying a price.

00:59:29.230 --> 00:59:31.429
Let that someone be you.

00:59:32.590 --> 00:59:35.269
Peace is the result of people going out of their way

00:59:35.269 --> 00:59:36.550
to maintain peace.

00:59:36.550 --> 00:59:40.539
It's not an accident.

00:59:40.539 --> 00:59:44.179
Someone is sacrificing self interest.

00:59:44.179 --> 00:59:46.420
Let that someone be you.

00:59:46.420 --> 00:59:47.260
Why not?

00:59:48.420 --> 00:59:51.500
Take the time also to encourage those

00:59:51.500 --> 00:59:55.500
that you know are going out of their way to make peace.

00:59:55.500 --> 00:59:58.019
You know who they are, do not ignore them.

00:59:59.179 --> 01:00:00.739
Perhaps the one that volunteers

01:00:00.739 --> 01:00:02.219
to take a smaller workspace,

01:00:02.219 --> 01:00:05.739
though they have this seniority for a larger one.

01:00:07.219 --> 01:00:10.579
Or the one that feels they've been overlooked

01:00:10.579 --> 01:00:14.300
for a privilege they've been passed over,

01:00:14.300 --> 01:00:17.900
and yet they don't stop working with all their power

01:00:17.900 --> 01:00:20.940
in whatever work they are given.

01:00:20.940 --> 01:00:25.619
Their journey with Jehovah reveals who they are.

01:00:26.619 --> 01:00:31.619
And Jehovah is taking them to wonderful spiritual places.

01:00:34.139 --> 01:00:37.619
Jacob's challenges do not end with Uncle Laban.

01:00:39.260 --> 01:00:43.420
At 97 years old, and after 20 years of strife and tension,

01:00:43.420 --> 01:00:47.539
no doubt Jacob urns for peace as he heads home.

01:00:48.500 --> 01:00:52.380
But his journey with Jehovah now brings him face-to-face

01:00:52.380 --> 01:00:54.940
with yet another lesson.

01:00:56.179 --> 01:00:58.219
Here's the situation.

01:00:58.219 --> 01:01:03.219
His brother Esau, and his 400 men are advancing toward Jacob.

01:01:03.219 --> 01:01:08.219
All Jacob remembers is that Esau told Mom he would kill me.

01:01:09.980 --> 01:01:12.500
Jacob is up all night, tired and scared.

01:01:12.500 --> 01:01:13.739
Facing such a crisis,

01:01:13.739 --> 01:01:17.019
imagine the relief when an angel appears.

01:01:17.019 --> 01:01:18.380
Good, an angel.

01:01:18.380 --> 01:01:21.460
Surely this angel is here to strengthen me.

01:01:21.460 --> 01:01:25.619
However, it seems that the angel wants to pick a fight.

01:01:26.860 --> 01:01:31.460
Now, chapter 32 and verse 24.

01:01:32.780 --> 01:01:33.780
Here it is.

01:01:33.780 --> 01:01:37.139
The man began to wrestle with me until the dawn broke.

01:01:37.139 --> 01:01:39.380
You want to wrestle with me now?

01:01:40.739 --> 01:01:42.340
Bad timing.

01:01:42.340 --> 01:01:45.260
But journeying with Jehovah in this case

01:01:45.260 --> 01:01:48.019
resulted in a crippling injury for Jacob.

01:01:48.019 --> 01:01:52.659
He would limp the rest of his life.

01:01:52.659 --> 01:01:56.780
But Jehovah saw fit for Jacob to have this experience

01:01:56.780 --> 01:01:58.780
at this time in his life.

01:02:00.219 --> 01:02:02.739
Perhaps to teach him humility.

01:02:02.739 --> 01:02:05.900
A constant reminder not to be overly exalted

01:02:05.900 --> 01:02:08.139
about his God-given prosperity,

01:02:08.139 --> 01:02:13.139
or the blessings that he would receive in the future.

01:02:14.139 --> 01:02:18.139
Now, Jacob didn't understand why Jehovah was allowing this.

01:02:19.579 --> 01:02:23.659
But he showed deep appreciation for spiritual things.

01:02:23.659 --> 01:02:26.139
Look what happens in verse 26.

01:02:26.139 --> 01:02:31.139
Even though his hip was dislocated, the man is in pain.

01:02:31.260 --> 01:02:33.059
And yet, verse 26 says,

01:02:33.059 --> 01:02:36.460
I'm not going to let you go until you bless me.

01:02:36.460 --> 01:02:41.460
Point, Jacob held on tighter after he was hurt.

01:02:41.460 --> 01:02:45.460
The man is hurt and he clung tighter to Jehovah.

01:02:45.460 --> 01:02:48.780
What was Jacob's blessing for doing this?

01:02:49.739 --> 01:02:51.539
A name change.

01:02:51.539 --> 01:02:53.059
Verse 28.

01:02:53.059 --> 01:02:55.940
Your name will be no longer Jacob, but Israel.

01:02:57.300 --> 01:03:00.019
But to Jacob, that was precious.

01:03:00.019 --> 01:03:02.780
He knew the name change had deep meaning.

01:03:02.780 --> 01:03:05.820
Abram to Abraham, Sarah to Sarah.

01:03:05.820 --> 01:03:10.139
And now Jacob to Israel, think about it.

01:03:10.139 --> 01:03:15.139
After Jehovah, no name in scripture is used more than Israel.

01:03:17.579 --> 01:03:20.539
True, many of those occurrences refer to the nation,

01:03:20.539 --> 01:03:23.900
but the name of the nation, including spiritual Israel,

01:03:23.900 --> 01:03:26.820
came from the man, Jacob.

01:03:27.900 --> 01:03:32.099
Because Jacob held tight despite the pain,

01:03:32.099 --> 01:03:33.699
despite the hurt.

01:03:33.699 --> 01:03:36.619
Jehovah brought him to a spiritual place.

01:03:36.659 --> 01:03:40.460
He could have never reached on his own.

01:03:41.460 --> 01:03:42.699
The lesson for you.

01:03:43.739 --> 01:03:48.739
At times, your blessings are disguised as trials.

01:03:49.980 --> 01:03:53.579
In order for you to be more useful to Jehovah God,

01:03:53.579 --> 01:03:58.579
he may allow a series of events to unfold in your life

01:03:59.699 --> 01:04:02.019
and the events could be painful.

01:04:02.860 --> 01:04:06.460
Perhaps you receive counsel that hurts.

01:04:07.340 --> 01:04:09.860
Your reputation is questioned.

01:04:09.860 --> 01:04:13.380
Your spirit may be broken, your dignity pummeled.

01:04:13.380 --> 01:04:15.940
When the strongest instinct is to give up, walk away.

01:04:15.940 --> 01:04:17.900
I don't need this.

01:04:17.900 --> 01:04:19.380
Hold on tight.

01:04:19.380 --> 01:04:20.860
Don't let go.

01:04:20.860 --> 01:04:23.820
Kling to Jehovah, no matter the hurt.

01:04:23.820 --> 01:04:26.179
Learn the lesson of humility.

01:04:26.179 --> 01:04:27.340
Pray, stay busy.

01:04:27.340 --> 01:04:30.820
Keep moving forward with God's spirit-directed organization.

01:04:30.820 --> 01:04:32.579
Fight for that reward.

01:04:33.780 --> 01:04:35.500
What reward?

01:04:35.500 --> 01:04:41.980
For a future blessing that only can come from Jehovah.

01:04:41.980 --> 01:04:46.980
At times, we may feel like Jacob when he told Pharaoh,

01:04:47.460 --> 01:04:50.219
the years of my life have been few and distressing.

01:04:51.340 --> 01:04:54.179
However, and despite all the hardships

01:04:54.179 --> 01:04:56.900
that this man experienced just before his death,

01:04:56.900 --> 01:04:59.820
what did the man Jacob say?

01:04:59.860 --> 01:05:03.179
He said, the true God has been shepherding me

01:05:03.179 --> 01:05:05.139
all my life.

01:05:05.139 --> 01:05:06.539
What a journey.

01:05:06.539 --> 01:05:08.539
His journey with Jehovah God brought him

01:05:08.539 --> 01:05:13.940
no resentment, just gratitude.

01:05:13.940 --> 01:05:17.860
Now in conclusion, I have two points I want you to remember.

01:05:19.219 --> 01:05:24.659
Not for a written exercise,

01:05:24.659 --> 01:05:29.420
but I want these two points to be indelibly etched

01:05:29.420 --> 01:05:33.519
on your mind and heart.

01:05:33.559 --> 01:05:35.840
One, like Jacob.

01:05:37.360 --> 01:05:39.599
When you stumble into a patch of injustice

01:05:39.599 --> 01:05:42.360
or disappointment or unfair treatment,

01:05:42.360 --> 01:05:47.360
trust Jehovah will help you rise above fleshly tendencies

01:05:47.679 --> 01:05:52.300
and he will help you to grow spiritually.

01:05:52.300 --> 01:05:54.739
Let him take you past all the injustices

01:05:54.739 --> 01:05:56.380
to great spiritual blessings.

01:05:56.380 --> 01:06:01.489
It's the only way to come out a winner.

01:06:01.489 --> 01:06:04.489
And when you experience a hurtful situation,

01:06:05.489 --> 01:06:10.489
hold tightly to the promise that Jehovah God will reward you

01:06:10.489 --> 01:06:14.489
in due time for doing what is right.

01:06:15.489 --> 01:06:18.090
Stick to Jehovah.

01:06:18.090 --> 01:06:22.289
Stick with him even through the rough neighborhoods,

01:06:23.289 --> 01:06:25.730
the rocky roads, the uphill climbs,

01:06:25.730 --> 01:06:28.610
he'll not only help you with the hard parts of the journey,

01:06:28.610 --> 01:06:33.610
but again, he will take you to places spiritually,

01:06:34.210 --> 01:06:37.170
you can never get to on your own.

01:06:37.170 --> 01:06:39.610
That's the privilege, that's the point.

01:06:40.489 --> 01:06:44.369
More than 3,700 years after Jacob's death,

01:06:44.369 --> 01:06:47.449
let his life course please, we urge you

01:06:48.409 --> 01:06:51.650
to continue to teach you no matter what circumstances

01:06:51.650 --> 01:06:53.329
come your way.

01:06:53.329 --> 01:07:14.849
Keep journeying with Jehovah.

